  $( If three numbers are coprime, and the square of one is the product of the
     other two, then there is a formula for the other two in terms of ` gcd `
     and square.  (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 17-Apr-2014.) $)
  coprimeprodsq2 $p |- ( ( ( A e. ZZ /\ B e. NN0 /\ C e. NN0 ) /\
    ( ( A gcd B ) gcd C ) = 1 ) -> ( ( C ^ 2 ) = ( A x. B ) ->
      B = ( ( B gcd C ) ^ 2 ) ) ) $=
    ( cz wcel cn0 w3a cgcd co c1 wceq wa c2 cexp cmul zcn nn0cn mulcom 3adant3
    cc syl2an adantr eqeq2d wi simpl2 simpl1 simpl3 gcdcom oveq1d eqeq1d sylan2
    wb nn0z biimpa coprimeprodsq syl31anc sylbid ) ADEZBFEZCFEZGZABHIZCHIZJKZLZ
