  ${
    $d A n m k $.  $d B n m k $.  $d C n m k $.
    $( Lemma for ~ pythagtrip .  Prove a weaker version of one direction of the
       theorem.  (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 28-Mar-2014.) $)
    pythagtriplem1 $p |- (
       E. n e. NN E. m e. NN E. k e. NN
       ( A = ( k x. ( ( m ^ 2 ) - ( n ^ 2 ) ) ) /\
         B = ( k x. ( 2 x. ( m x. n ) ) ) /\
         C = ( k x. ( ( m ^ 2 ) + ( n ^ 2 ) ) ) ) ->
        ( ( A ^ 2 ) + ( B ^ 2 ) ) = ( C ^ 2 ) ) $=
      ( c2 cexp co cmin cmul wceq caddc cn wcel cc sqcl syl 2cn c4 cv w3a wa wi
      wrex nncn adantl mulcl syl2anr sylancr subcl syl2anc adantr add32 syl3anc
